    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    
    <p>This Privacy Statement for TechCentre is applicable to all customers and users of the TechCentre Network. This is a clear statement of TechCentre's approach to privacy.</p>
    <p>You do not have to give us personal data to access or use most of this web site. However, to access more specialist or personalised/customised areas of our web site, you may need to provide certain persona information.</p>
    <p>TechCentre respects the privacy of your personal information and guards your data carefully. Recognising that the growth of the Internet has created customer concern about the protection and use of information collected about them, TechCentre is committed to providing privacy protection to customer information collected online at TechCentre's web site (www.TechCentre.co.im).</p>
    <p>TechCentre's Privacy Statement sets forth the manner in which TechCentre handles and protects personally identifiable information (PII) received on-line. In addition to TechCentre's Privacy Statement, you may receive notice of specific terms that apply to particular services or promotions.</p>
    <p>Please read this Privacy Statement carefully as once you use our web site or our services you will be deemed to have read and accepted this Privacy Statement and the terms and conditions of use included on our web site.</p>
    <p>You must not use our web site or our services if you do not accept this Privacy Statement or the terms and conditions that are applicable to this web site.</p>

    <h2>Use of information collected</h2>
    <p>TechCentre may ask for some personally identifiable information about you when you visit our web site, such as your name, e-mail address or telephone number. TechCentre uses this information to maintain accurate accounts, provide services, bill and respond to questions presented. To express interest in our employment opportunities, we also enable users to submit resume information. TechCentre also uses the information collected for marketing purposes to inform them of new offers, products and services which may be of interest to you and to help us improve and personalise our services and any services provided to you through our services such as Service On-line. To carry out all of these uses, we may need to pass your information between our various TechCentre offices in various countries from time to time, however, such sharing of information shall be subject to this Privacy Policy and the terms and conditions that are applicable to this web site at any time.</p>
    <p>In addition, TechCentre may collect and share information about your visit to our web site in aggregated data that does not identify you specifically, in order to make our site more user friendly.</p>

    <h2>Passing on your information</h2>
    <p>Except as stated below, TechCentre does not currently share, disclose or sell personally identifiable information collected online with other companies or organisations. TechCentre may share personally identifiable information with agents or sub-contractors who have agreed to use the information only in a manner consistent with this privacy statement. In addition, TechCentre may disclose personally identifiable information in response to legal process or when it believes in good faith that the law requires it, for example, in response to a court order, subpoena or a law enforcement agency's request.</p>
    <p>Should TechCentre decide in the future to share customers' personally identifiable information with third parties in a manner different than stated here, it will post a revised privacy statement and provide its users with the opportunity to indicate their preference concerning TechCentre's sharing of their information. Should you give your consent to the sharing of your information, you may at any time ask TechCentre and the third parties who receive your information to stop providing such services to you.</p>

    <h2>Transfer of information abroad</h2>
    <p>Information supplied by you to TechCentre whether submitted by you via this or other web sites will only be transferred abroad by TechCentre or its group companies and agents for the purpose of performing contractual obligations owed by us to you or for the purposes outlined on this web site. You expressly agree to such transfer and acknowledge that such other countries may not have the same levels of data protection as the European Union although TechCentre will instruct any receiving parties to process any data in soley in accordance with TechCentre's instructions.</p>
    <p>Any data transmitted will be transmitted in encrypted format use secure socket layer technology.</p>

    <h2>Cookie Policy</h2>
    <p>TechCentre may use cookies on its web site so that it can track how its users navigate through its site in order that TechCentre can evaluate and improve its site by understanding your requirements and interests better. TechCentre may use the cookies to compile statistical data on the use of its web site but the information collated is used on an anonymous, aggregated basis and you cannot be identified from this.</p>
    <p>A cookie is a small data file which contains information about you that may be sent to your computer's hard drive. These cookies do not retrieve information about you which is stored upon your hard drive nor do they corrupt or damage your computer or computer files. You are not obliged to accept a cookie that TechCentre sends you but most browsers are set up to receive cookies automatically. You can in fact modify the functions on your browser so that it will not accept cookies (please see your Help function on your browser or contact your system administrator for more information).</p>
    <p>When you visit the TechCentre web site, the TechCentre server will record your IP address together with the time, date and duration of your visit. An IP address is an allocated number, similar to a phone number, which allows your computer to communicate over the internet. TechCentre may also use cookies on the web site to store passwords so that it is not necessary to provide a password on every visit to a password-protected area of our site.</p>

    <h2>Security</h2>

    <p>TechCentre has taken appropriate security measures to safeguard the personally identifiable information that we collect online. In addition, TechCentre does not market to children or knowingly collect personal information from children at this site.</p>
    <p>Keeping information about you secure is very important to TechCentre. However, no data transmission over the Internet can be guaranteed to be totally secure. As a result, whilst TechCentre strive to protect your personal information, TechCentre cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information that you send to TechCentre, and you therefore do so at your own risk. You may therefore wish to consider whether to send confidential or sensitive information via the internet. Once TechCentre receives your transmission, all reasonable efforts are made to ensure its security on TechCentre's systems.</p>
    
    <h2>Updating and removing your details</h2>
    <p>You may review or update or correct the available PII that is received from you online through the TechCentre contact information below. In order to safeguard your PII, TechCentre will take steps to verify your identity before granting access.</p>
    <p>You may request that your information be removed from TechCentre information databases at any time by requesting such removal through the TechCentre's contact information below.</p>
    <p>TechCentre will always let you have a copy of all personal information TechCentre has about you should you request it. There will be an administration fee of £10 for such a request to cover the costs we incur in providing you with such data.</p>
    
    <p>For questions concerning the TechCentre Privacy Statement, please <asp:HyperLink ID="HyperLink1" runat="server" NavigateUrl="~/Contact.aspx">contact us</asp:HyperLink>.</p>
    
